Source-backed packages are Beanstalk source under `lib/`. Each direct child folder becomes an import prefix.

### A simple package

[codeblock, $code("text"):
    lib/
    └── blog/
        ├── #api.bst
        └── helpers/dates.bst
]

`#api.bst` is just a cosmetic root filename. Any `#*.bst` name works.

### Importing from a package

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    import @blog {post_title}
]

`@blog` resolves to `lib/blog/`. The package's public surface comes from its export block.

### Remember

- `lib/` is the default package folder.
- Each direct child becomes a prefix.
- Internal files are hidden unless re-exported.
- Imported package roots do not become HTML routes.
